<br>
When you are talking about actual VL camps, such as uppers, village, etc, low level warriors should not be there.  The named mobs, as well as regular mobs, hit too hard and have too much hit points to handle.  They also are higher level, cannot be taunted off as easily.<br>
<br>
I was a level 54 tank one time in village, and I had a very tough time keeping aggro.  I couldn't keep aggro well in village until my current level of 57.<br>
<br>
Low level warriors with crusty armor and Centi LS's come into VL all the time.  Stereotyping occurs out of good reason.  These tanks will get chewed up, assuming they can keep aggro, in  the tougher camps.  <br>
<br>
Old Sebilis is the same way.  Sure, a lower level warrior can tank in a GoZ group, but they will be more of a mana sponge, which in turn will inhibit killing speed due to cleric mana.  Low level warrior can't take very well in King at all.<br>
<br>
Low level warriors have trouble grouping because sooner or later a higher level tank will come in.  There are plenty of warriors, and many groups will pass up a 52 war lfg and wait for a 59 war lfg, and this can vary depending on camp difficulty.<br>
<br>
I'm starting to ramble...but the bottom line is this.  Grouping is tough because these two zones have some camps that are higher level, so some possibilities are cut there.  Also, there are other tanks competing with you that will get the job done.  That's just how it is.   <p><b>Lochraven<b><br>
